# Window: hashchange event

The `hashchange` event is ==fired when the fragment identifier of the URL has changed (the part of the URL beginning with and following the `#` symbol)==.

## Syntax

Use the event name in methods like [`addEventListener()`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget/addEventListener), or set an _event handler property_:

```js
addEventListener('hashchange', (event) => {});
// or
onhashchange = (event) => {};
```

## Event type

A [`HashChangeEvent`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HashChangeEvent). Inherits from [`Event`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Event).

